webpackJsonp([94047473995071],{429:function(e,t){e.exports={data:{site:{siteMetadata:{title:"John D Potts",author:"John Potts"}},markdownRemark:{id:"C:/Users/John/programming/gatsby-starter-blog/src/pages/2018-05-26-self-teaching/index.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark",html:'<p>\n  <a\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-link"\n    href="/static/sign-d0f542bf8bcecc1b2f4eb1b228a55e57-9b65b.jpeg"\n    style="display: block"\n    target="_blank"\n    rel="noopener"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-wrapper"\n    style="position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 420px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"\n  >\n    <span\n      class="gatsby-resp-image-background-image"\n      style="padding-bottom: 66.66666666666666%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(\'data:image/jpeg;base64,\'); background-size: cover; display: block;"\n    >\n      <img\n        class="gatsby-resp-image-image"\n        style="width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;"\n        alt="Sign"\n        title=""\n        src="/static/sign-d0f542bf8bcecc1b2f4eb1b228a55e57-2d9c5.jpeg"\n        srcset="/static/sign-d0f542bf8bcecc1b2f4eb1b228a55e57-905e5.jpeg 105w,\n/static/sign-d0f542bf8bcecc1b2f4eb1b228a55e57-3a98f.jpeg 210w,\n/static/sign-d0f542bf8bcecc1b2f4eb1b228a55e57-2d9c5.jpeg 420w,\n/static/sign-d0f542bf8bcecc1b2f4eb1b228a55e57-64cc3.jpeg 630w,\n/static/sign-d0f542bf8bcecc1b2f4eb1b228a55e57-19d8a.jpeg 840w,\n/static/sign-d0f542bf8bcecc1b2f4eb1b228a55e57-a8185.jpeg 1260w,\n/static/sign-d0f542bf8bcecc1b2f4eb1b228a55e57-9b65b.jpeg 1920w"\n        sizes="(max-width: 420px) 100vw, 420px"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>In my experience mentoring emerging developers in the tech community, I run into one question over and over:</p>\n<hr>\n<h3>“What (if any) bootcamp should I attend?</h3>\n<hr>\n<p>While I believe that developer bootcamps have their place (and are, in fact, an excellent alternative to a multi-year degree program at a traditional university), I know for a fact that they aren’t a requirement for someone seeking to make a career transition into development. How do I know this? <strong>Because I did it.</strong></p>\n<p>I moved from a career in a completely different industry to a career as a full-time Front End developer without attending a college or boot camp. I had a few great folks who fielded questions for me and offered excellent advice, but no actual mentor. </p>\n<p>I don’t have anything against boot camps per say; in fact I briefly considered attending one, but as the sole income-earner in a family with kids I just couldn’t justify the cost and the need to miss work for months to attend an in-person boot camp.</p>\n<p>What’s the secret? How did I transition careers without attending a structured program? Well,first let’s consider what a bootcamp provides; after all, there are all kinds of resources for learning web development that are available for free or a minimal cost online.</p>\n<p>Here’s what you’re paying for in a bootcamp:</p>\n<h4>1.  An environment that encourages you to focus on learning</h4>\n<h4>2.  A community to learn along with</h4>\n<h4>3.  A clear road map of what you should be learning</h4>\n<h4>4.  Mentoring and guidance from instructors</h4>\n<h4>5.  A network (and hopefully job leads) in the local area</h4>\n<p>My thought process was simply this- would I, and could I, replicate those things? If so, would it be worth what I would pay to go to a boot camp? For me, the answer was yes.</p>\n<p>The decision I made isn’t for everyone. I think well-run development boot camps have a great deal to offer, especially if you learn best in a classroom-type setting. But for me, it wasn’t the best fit, and I’m glad to have gone through the effort of learning on my own.</p>\n<p><strong>In a future post I’ll explore the strategy I pursued over 5 months of self-teaching that brought me to my first development role.</strong></p>',excerpt:"In my experience mentoring emerging developers in the tech community, I run into one question over and over: “What (if any) bootcamp should…",fields:{slug:"/2018-05-26-self-teaching/"},frontmatter:{title:"Should You Attend a Developer Bootcamp?",date:"May 26, 2018",featuredImage:{childImageSharp:{sizes:{src:"/static/sign-d0f542bf8bcecc1b2f4eb1b228a55e57-75c44.jpeg"}}}}}},pathContext:{slug:"/2018-05-26-self-teaching/",previous:{fields:{slug:"/2018-05-19-developer-strengths/"},frontmatter:{title:"Essential Developer Strengths"}},next:{fields:{slug:"/2018-06-02-design-patterns-1/"},frontmatter:{title:"Design Patterns in JS: The Module Pattern"}}}}}});
